# Document Contract Template

**Purpose**: Define a standardized interface for documentation generation tasks within the Context eXchange System.

## Contract Metadata

- **Name**: document
- **Version**: 1.0.0
- **Type**: Documentation Generation
- **Created**: 2025-10-04
- **Status**: Active Template

## Description

This contract defines the expectations and interface for generating documentation from source materials, code, or analysis results in various formats and styles.

## Inputs

| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |
|-----------|------|----------|-------------|
| source_material | path/reference | Yes | Content to be documented |
| doc_type | string | Yes | Type of documentation (API, user guide, technical) |
| template_spec | path | No | Documentation template or style guide |
| output_format | string | Yes | Target format (markdown, html, pdf) |

## Outputs

| Artifact | Type | Location | Description |
|----------|------|----------|-------------|
| documentation | document | outbox/ | Primary documentation output |
| source_map | json | outbox/ | Mapping of content to source materials |
| generation_log | text | outbox/ | Documentation generation process log |
| quality_report | markdown | outbox/ | Documentation quality assessment |

## Validation Gates

1. **Source Validation**: Source material is accessible and parseable
2. **Content Validation**: Generated content is complete and accurate
3. **Format Validation**: Output conforms to specified format standards
4. **Quality Validation**: Documentation meets readability and completeness criteria

## Provenance

- **Source Materials**: Document all input sources and their versions
- **Generation Method**: Record documentation generation approach
- **Template Version**: Track template or style guide versions used
- **Content Lineage**: Map generated content back to source elements

## Success Criteria

- All source material successfully processed
- Documentation generated in specified format
- Content is accurate and comprehensive
- Quality metrics indicate acceptable readability
- Output validates against format specifications

## Error Handling

- Inaccessible source material → Log error, skip unavailable sections
- Format conversion failure → Log error, attempt alternative formats
- Template processing error → Log warning, use default formatting
- Quality threshold not met → Log warning, flag for human review

## Notes

- This is a generic documentation contract template
- Customize content types and quality criteria for specific documentation needs
- Consider accessibility and internationalization requirements
- Version contracts when documentation standards change